✅ Updated Link to Binary to Decimal converter with plain html, js and css.

Binary is the number system all digital computers are based on. Therefore it's important for developers to understand binary, or base 2, mathematics. The purpose of Bin2Dec is to provide practice and understanding of how binary calculations.

✅ Bin2Dec allows the user to enter strings of up to 8 binary digits, 0's and 1's, in any sequence and then displays its decimal equivalent.

-This challenge requires that the developer implementing it follow these constraints:

✅ Arrays may not be used to contain the binary digits entered by the user
✅ Determining the decimal equivalent of a particular binary digit in the sequence must be calculated using a single mathematical function, for example the natural logarithm. It's up to you to figure out which function to use.

# Blood Donation Application

**Tier:** 2-Intermediate

An application that allows users to donate blood to the National Blood Services (NBS) of their respective country. This applicaiton would allow users
to create user profiles, register their blood type, input useful information required when donating blood to assess their elligibility. Users also
have the ability to donate blood to specific individuals who request blood.


## User Stories

-   [ ] User can enter a username
-   [ ] User can schedule an appointment to donate blood.
-   [ ] User can request blood donation and other users can fulfil this request.
-   [ ] User can view the areas on a map where they can make donations in their given city.

## Bonus features
-  [ ] User can toggle dark/light mode
-  [ ] Users can receive notifications about when NBS is in their area.
-  [ ] A system that allows users to earn points and collect rewards.

## Useful links and resources

- [National Blood Services](https://www.blood.gov.au/)

## Bug Tracker Project

**Level:** 3-Advanced

### Overview

Bug trackers are widely used by developers from all areas of technology. The idea seems simple on the surface, but as we dig deeper into how the system works and what features a robust bug tracker should contain, more complex concepts emerge.

Because of the variable levels of complexity that a bug tracker project can have depending on how far down the rabbit hole we go, I always like to recommend this as a good first or second project at the "advanced" level. For one, it ties together multiple programming concepts like UI design/development, back-end data modeling, potential database usage, state management, and more. Also, bug tracker projects have lots of good "stopping points" where code can be pushed and used while starting to do research for the next feature, which may itself be on a different complexity level.

### PR Details

I think the Markdown file that I've put together is a great guide to building a basic bug tracker application and I think that it also leaves enough room for a high level of individualization from project to project. 

I'd love any suggestions or additions if we think there is anything that should be added for a basic bug tracker application. There's certainly room for more advanced features and functionality here, but I'm uncertain whether we should list out more possibilities under the "Bonus Features" section or leave them up to the imagination of the folks building the application.

Thanks!
